betterquesting:10.desc:8: So here you are. Bannished from your land, for ever strip of the right to walk freely. In this... prison. They said that it is a maze of dimensions and twisted worlds where no technology works. They hope you will just give it up and die. You! I can tell you something, I obey the legal system, but this is just too much. This calls for a revolution. But fist, how to get out of here? Well, you are not just master of technomancy but also master of arcana. So... Let's blast your way out. The only question is, how big boom will you need?

Well hopefully you know how to survive now. And you are free for some experiments. As I told you previously we will need to do some booms to get out of here. Make sure you have good access to TNT since this crude and basic explosive will be core of our first bunch of tests.
First, let's try the most simple way. Will this move the fabric of reality? Build nether poral. Surround it with TNT and prime i with a lightning using your new PSI powers.

betterquesting:10.name:8: The other end of the Portal
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Nether portal seems to be not enough to even move the fabric of reality. Let's try something harder. Build an Aether portal, using Glowstone and Bucket of Water and blast it with at least two simultaniously flying primed TNT carts.

Enough child games. Let's do some serious business. If blasting through portal is not enough we should try maybe sacrifice. Collect some good ingrediences. As listed bellow. Then build an altar above a lavapool. In the center of your altar place a milkpool... surround it with living rock, livingwood and silverwood. The shape and decoration I will leave to your own imagination. Then... put your sacrifice (yes, live one) in the milkpool. Also throw in the pool all the items, set it ablaze and blast it using all the suggested methods simultaneously. Let's see if this will move the fabric of reality or not.

Let's try different portal and increase the explosion magnitude using some alumentum. Build the Tropico portal by drinking pinacolada at sunset and sitting in the beach chair. This will spawn a 2x2 tropical portal well. Let's mutilate it for our need. Build an altar around the well. Push in it your next (yes, live) sacrifice, toss in suggested items and blast it using alumentum and Flare Flower Explosion wand.

The stronger explosive was a good idea and it loks that the sacrificed items were also better. On the other hand the Tropical Portal was just wrong. Well let's try something different. Build a Twilight portal and surroud it by altar with full mana cart. Use Ender Eye Staff as a sacrifice, add some alchymical powder. Push there at least 4 Charged Creepers and blast it all using Mana bursts.

We are running out of portals to try. Hmm... but we still have some spatial distortions we might try to open more than was ever conscidered to be possible. Let's blow up Elven Portal. Build altar using runic totems, sparks and braziers. Add mass using artificial planet. Sacrifice some mana and few other carfully selected artefacts and blow it up using Big Bombs.

Next Experiment. Build a Celestial Gateway in Tropical Island. Surround it with altar using some Special Gold, Corporeal Funels and Beacons. Use Void Tear and some few other things as a sacrifice and blow it up using Hexamite. Mix in some Lightning Strikes and rain some Holy Handgranades.

If they think that you are out of ideas, they are WRONG. Here is first crazy one. Make altar IN THE AETHER, using given blocks. Centered around the Inspiration Machine. Toss around the items suggested here and sacrifice the Black Hole (andmaybe some local animals)... the best propellant for now is probable the Heximite.

Crazy Idea... but if you place Thaumcraft Gate portal under water in Tropical Dimension? Add altar using Sea Lanterns and some Daemon Stones. Blow it up using the good old Hexamite... that has to work, right? Right?

Ha... New Explosives. Let's mix it into the show. Here is an idea. Go to the Nether. Build a secret laboratory with some Priporial Acelerators. Use Void Beacon as the center stone of the lab. And use suggested explosives to simulate a proper Lab Accident.

Yes, this is not safe. So, don't do it at home. Find some island far away and do it there. Build one of those newly discovered Mystical portals. Activate it, surround it with an altar, where center piece will be the Madness Machine. Do the sacrifice and blow it up. You probably know the drill by now.

And we have a new dimension to play with. Ok, I have the just right things in mind to build the altar. Center it around the druids altar you crafted. And sacrifice the strange cloth you read about. Use the new explosives.
Well your visit in the Betweenlands had unexpected outcome. You now can create a new much stronger explosive. And I have in mind just the right altar to test it on.

Well, this is also an option. This altar should have an Eldritch pedestal in it's middle with a Wormhole mirror on it. Add some recommended blocks and some recommended sacrifices. Blow it up using your new most favourite explosive.
In your last experiments you neglected the sacrificial part a lot. It is time to fix this and dig deeper into what all can be destroyed in the name of progress. Do this altar in the betweenland.

Maybe you finally found the best place for your Big Boom. In the Mystical Dimensions you noticed a Fissure leading somewhere else. Only if you could open that tear in reality a little bit more. Build altar from recommended blocks and do the sacrifice... well, you know the drill. This time let's try to poke some time tweaking aparatus

Well... there is one last rift you could try to blow up.But I am not sure if it is worth the risk. If you will overload a thaumic flux field it will tier appart the fabric of space and create a Spatial Rift. You ould try to create an altar near such rift. Use Dislocator pedestal as a centerpiece. I am giving you the list of ingrediences as allways.

Last experiments show that you are on the right track. Fissure probably in combination with Rift are the solution. Just the boom is still not enough. What if it is only about how much energy you can blow up on one spot? Build at least Tier 4 energy core above a draconic portal. Build altar, where the core will be it's center piece. Toss the sacrifice and blow it all up.

All the experiments lead to this. There is no other way how to put this much energy into this little space. The biggest eplosion above the wildest tears in universe. Find a Fissure and force a Flux Rift right nxt to it. Build an altar where the center piece will be the Draconic Power Reactor. Use recommended blocks. Place demon wills on the Spectral Relays nearby. Trigger the reactor overload... an here you are... you are the winner of the game.
Many players has issue reading storybook, since they don't know if/how they will survive the night. So, here is something to help you start and now make time to read me, ok?

So you have time to read? Good. Here is what I want to tell you. This is a simple modpack. I restricted myself extensively to keep it simple so don't be surprised. This Questing book is not here to guide you as much as you might be used from other modpacks. It is here for 3 reasons. 1) Tell you some story so you get more from the game. 2) Give you hints which mods you should try and how to start with them next. 3) Warn you about the few gates I introduced into this game. Now there are 2 parts of this book... The chapters at the top are the Story Chapters. This bottom one is the mod progress guide.

First thing you should know about this world is that it's resources are spread unevently. Under desert are different deposites than under ice plains. But All resources are with at least in small ammounts everywhere and in every height. So don't bother with digging too deep to find diamonds they are in the same ammount also just under the surface. Now, some mods to start with. At the begginning you can improve your life with ExNihilo, Monk mod, Tinkers Construct, Eb Wizardry, Psi and Root.
Anoher great starting mod is Monk Mod... become first grade monk by punching wood... if you will get 10 wood by fist, you will level up. Follow Monk Quests in your achievement tab.
By building tinkers tool station you will unlock simple and achievable tools which can level up and be repaired. Try flint tools for start.

Electroblobs Wizardry is a straight forward magical mod. Get the wand and cast spells. Spells drop from mobs. Wand is charged by crystals in the altar. The only downside is the altar which is not as trivial to make. Later on you will want to upgrade your wand. For that I added some recipes. You might try the original way but it didn't work when I last checked.

Psi is very special "Program your spell" way of doing magic. Start by making the one table you can and by turning a rod into a wand in the table. Turn redstone in the magic powder using this wand. Then make the other table and follow the magic book instructions. This book can be opened using some shortcut, "C" by default. Try to find it out. Also the same shortcut, when holding your wand will allow you to select the spell. Best if you watch some basic video tutorial.

If you want something more alchymical... you can start with druid magic. It is all about collecting some basic resources from the nature and mixing them into spells. Also the most basic healing is here. All is writen in the tablet. Read it.

This mod gives you sieves and hammers. Hammer cobble to gravel, sand and dust. Use sieve with various meshes to sieve-out resources. Also try compressed variants. Crook leaves to get more saplings and some silkworms. Use silkworms to turn leaves into string source. Don't forget to see some tutorials online.

Gates are recipes, which are changed by the modpack maker (me - mu ha ha ha) to focus your efforts. Simply before I will allow you to do B, you have to first do A. Let me give you the first examples: I gated Easy Botania behind Twilight Forrest. I gated Tinkers Construct Smeltery behind Psi and Basic Botania. And I gated Embers Rekindeled behind Nether or Twilight forrest. To learn more, read about those mods in the subs-quests.

This is huge magical dimension, where you progress by hunting enemy bosses. There is a sequence in which you are allowed to kill the bosses. So if you will suddenly start dying just by entering a fog or rain, it is because you wandered somewhere you are not supposed to go yet. The sequence of bosses is visible in the achievements table. To enter Twilight forrest make pool 2x2 of water (all around grass) plant minecraft flowers around the pool and toss in a diamond. It should turn into the portal and a lightning should strike the ground. Why to go there? Well, first you can get fireflies there which is important for Floral Fertilizer. Also there is Bedrock. Did you noticed that there is no bedrock in the overworld? And it is also a lot of fun and adventure to be there.

There are some resouces which are not common in overworld. Namely Nether Quartz, Glowstone and Bedrock. All can be found also in the Nether. Portal is as usual 2x3, surrounded with Obsidian, and fire it up using Flint and Steel. Beware, Nether is inhabited by some quite nasty monsters.

Another Techno-magic mod. It has some nice early automation stuff, like pipes and pumps. It has ore doubling and stamping mechanics. It also has unique item repair system and some powerfull weapons and gadgets. It can smelt and alloy simmilarly as tinkers construct smeltery. Start by building the guide tablet... and by mining some ember using the ember quarry. See video tutorial to get the details on how. Hint: Ember Bore has tu be placed above Bedrock.

Maybe you noticed that it is quite hard to make any food. Too many recipes, too many foods to choose from. Don't worry, there is an easy way to get through it. Build a kitchen. Mods are called Harvestcraft and Cooking for blockheads. Check the videos if you will not want to figure it yourself. It is not too much hard.

And quite powerful one. Botania is your first Techno-magic mod. it contains automation, gadgets and powerful tools and armor. It has deep ingame guide. What is tricky is tha you need to start by getting 4 white petalts to make first Pure Daisy flower. Well to get petalt you have to find White Flowers... White Mushrooms... or get Floral Fertilizer. So travel the world and search... or go to Twilight Forrest to get the fertilizer.

Tinkers smeltery and Tool Forge are gateway to better materials and better tinkers tools. To build them you have to first manage some Botania and Psi since they are neded for the Grout. When you will have the Grout, cook it and follow the instructions in the tinkers construct book. A pro po, do you know there is also armor forge?

Another Wand and Altar based magic mod present is the Astral Sorcery. There is no gate hiding this mod except that you need to find an Astral Sorcery Shrine to start with... and have base nearby. Astral sorcery has also in game guide but this one is more poetic and less practical. I recommend watching video tutorials and visit community page: minecraftguides.net/AS ... but for quick start: Build the Wand in a crafting table placed nearby the crystal you will find in the shrine. Build the book in the same crafting table. Make the Lumious Crafting table using the guide in the book. And what this mod can do? Healing rituals, Growth rituals, Teleportation, Tools, Some Automation, Flight... it is quite large.

There are more realms to visit then just Twilight and Nether. Next are Aether (Yes The Haeven) and Tropico. After all you deserve some time off, right? Well, take your best pew-pew wand with you. You will need it. Some details about both dimensions are in the subquests.

There are two even more complex Magical Mods included in this pack. To get to it's end you will have to explore sooner or later both. Thaumcraft is an alchemy-like techno-arcana mod. There is automation, Better smelting, Item doubling, and a lot of powerfull gadgets. Blood magic is altar and ritual based mod, all about colecting life essence and using it to power your magic. It has also automation and various rituals and gadgets.

This is the last bunch of dimensions on your journey. The End is quite straight forward, just craft End Cake, place it and eat it. Beware, this is Draconic Evolution End... the nasty one. Don't venture far beyond the main island. The other two available dimensions are Betweenlands and Erebus read more about them in the subquests. Both those dimensions are gated behind Thaumcraft and Blood magic so you will need to progress in them first.

Now you know all about dimensions... almost. Well did you know that you can your own dimensions? You can. Mod is called Mystcraft and now you have all to start using it. Make the ink mixer, and book binder. Later on you will also need the Table for collected dimension pages. To start, put bottle of ink and some paper into the ink mixer and get a binding page. If you will craft this page with a piece of leather, you will get linking page. This is like a fast personal teleporter. Right click it and it will bind to the place you are standing on. Place it in a book stand anywhere and click it to teleport back here. Now how to make a dimension. Use the book binder. Place there a leather and the linking page. This is simple, random, dimension book. In every dimension you wisit look for mystical library. It will contain Dimensional Pages. By adding those pages into your books you can bend what the new dimension should be like.

There are multiple reasons why to go to Aether. First, it is another great source for Botania Flowers and It is the only source of Ambrosium. Those are needed for Mystical Aggriculture basic seeds. Mystical seeds are magical seeds which grow resources. Any resources. Try some and be amazed. You will be able to access tier 1-3 with Aether resources. To get there build 2x3 portal of Glowstone and fire it up with a Water Bucket.

This is another great place to visit. Beware the mobs are quite hard. Later on there will be some resources you cannot find anywhere else bu here so don't hasitate and visit that beautiful place. As directly gated mod you can then build EnderStorage Chests and Tanks. To get to Tropic you need to find bamboo, coconut tree and pineapple plants. The coconut is the hardest. You might need to buy in the Harvestcraft Market. But that is not the right coconut. The right one must be crafted using Botania terrasteel. Place a coconut and break it with sword to get the coconut chunk. Craft Pinacolada and Beach Chair. Drink it at sunset and sit in the chair. Beware, on the same spot 4x4 portal will spawn.

To start with thaumcraft you need to make Salis Mundus and toss it over a bookcase block. You will get Thaumonomicon. The great and extensive in game guide. Every page has in it's left bottom corner what you have to do to uncover that chapter. There are various possible tasks like get item, or travel somewhere. If you will get lost, check some videos for Thaumcraft 6.

This mod is all about life and daemons. To learn more ingame, you can craft the guide book. Or watch the videos. But essentialy you need to start by collecting Wills. This is done by killing mobs using the Snare. When you will have some will you can make the Hellforge and build your Lesser Tartaric Gem. When you will collect some more will, you can create your first Blood Altar and Week Orb.

Erebus is a strange cave-like world full of mysterious creaures and ancient monuments. To get there build the altar. Place on it diamond, obsidian and emerald to get the Gem. Make the Staff and Keystone... make a portal frame and fill it with leaves. Place the Staff in a keystone nearby and voila. There is Achievement guide system for the Erebus.

The Betweenland is even more large adventure dimension than Twilight forrest. It is mystical and spooky. And you need to explore it if you want to progress further. To get there FIND the altar. It spawns usually in the Swamps. Then use end-level Root magic to craft all 4 parts of the talisman. put the parts into the altar and it will assemble the wand. Now by using the wand on a planted sapling you will grow a HUGE portal tree. So do it somewhere safe please, not in your livingroom.

Immersive Engineering is your first available techno-mod. To start it you need to build Coke Oven and Blast Furnace. Get the Manual to read all about the mod. It is quite thorrough. The mod has many gadgets but mainly it contains automation and industrial marvels.

Ender IO is your second Tech-mod. Unfortunately this mod has no ingame wiki so if you want to read more, you have to go to web. Tutorials, Mod Spotlights and EnderIO Wiki will help you. In short, this mod has all. Neat conduit system, ore processing, automation, storage solutions, spawners, teleportation and gadgets. To start, make Grains of Infinity by setting bedrock on fire and wait. Make first crude SAG mill (crusher) and Alloy Furnace.

And how to end this show differently than with the Draconic Eolution mod. This mod is so OverPowered that even your magical skills will soon look like a child's play. But to get here is not easy and it will be some work to make this count. You can look forward to super armor and tools, neat spawner-killer system, teleportation and more. Your final goal will be to Kill the Chaos Guardian... just venture to coordinates 10000 x 0 in end dimension in any direction and prepare for the biggest fight of your life. Maybe watch some tutorial first. To start with this mod, make the tablet which knows all.

Project E or Project Equivalence is a very old mod which reveals the one biggest true to every mage: Everything is power and power is everything. In a nutshell, this mod gives you the transmutation tablet which allows you to convert almost every item in game into it's EMC value and recreate the item back using the given EMC. This way you can convert 1000 Stone (EMC 1 each) to one Iron (EMC 1000). There are other things in this mod but you have to discover them yourelf, or use the wiki since there is no in game book.
Simple mod called Tree Growth Simulator allows you to speed-up tree growth by twerking... just stand next to a sapling and crouch-stand-crouch-...
SimpleCrafter mod is a simple block which will craft for you. Try it, maybe it will help.
There are multiple mods to make your creations even more beautiful. There is Platforms mod, ArchitectureCraft, Chisel and Builders Wands. Try them, they are quite intuitive.

There is one very straight-forward mod fo moving your items and liquids. It is called Translocators and it is Amazing. It can filter, it can transfer only specific amount, it can be redstone sensitive. Really, it is that easy. Only limitation, it can move stuff only one block away, no more.

Chunk is piece of your miecraft world. It is a square... well... chunk of world. And here is the funny part. If you are not near a chunk it saves itself into memory and waits. Soo... if you think you will have a beautiful garden and everything will grow while you are adventuring, you are wrong. It is saved in memory and waiting. But there is a solution. The solution is called ChunkLoader.

Bibliocraft mod is a huge collection of blocks with mostly storage and display purpouse. You can sit on the chairs, put books into the shelfs e.t.c. Most interresting is the duo of Printing Press and Typesetting Table. They allow you duplicate enchanted books. This and many more... read about it on their wiki.

Drawers, Chest Transporter, ProjectE Chest and Iron Backpacks. Those are mods you should check out if you are thinking about beter handling of items. ProjectE has the largest chest of all... and it is very accessible. Drawers mod gives you system of storage drawers which can be tweaked in many ways to cover your needs. Iron backpacks are dream personal inventory expansion solution.

There are Two mos giving you powerful reliqs even in the early game. One is ProjectE and the second one is Reliquiary. ProjectE is extremly advanced mod... but its Philosophers Stone is available quite early. It can transmute basic blocks. Try it out. Reliquiary is mod giving you various Staffs and Amulets. Well you must gether the material for them first and the materal drops from mobs.

Tombstone mod gives you grave which protects all your gear in case you die. It also gives you key which can safely lead you to your grave. If you want, you can also enchant that key and then it will be able to TELEPORT you there so you don't have to walk all the way. Also we have Light Overlay mod, try pressing F4 or find it out in the key config.

We have Two other mods than Monk for straight forward improving your Steve. Everlasting abilities and Improvable Skills. Abilities are hidden in that blue book in your inventory. Skills are those golden statues you get so often. Out of those two, abilities are the more expensive in the sense of XP. But adding Skills increases your hunger... so when you will need tons of food one day, you will know why and don't be surprised. But hey, three thousands Skills - that is worth it, trust me.
Sort of. This mod is called Vies craft and it allows you to build small airships. Try it out. It contains a manual so you can read it also in-game.

To make your estate even more interresting, you can utilize those two mods. Redstone Gauges and Switches contains infinite ammount of variable levers and pullys. Tinkers Workshop gives you Drawbridge block which places blocks you specify in it's UI if you give it redstone signal.
Start here to learn what's up
We tried the most basic. It does not work. Let's push a little bit more, shell we?
All jokes aside. What is left is pure maddness but it is the only thing you can try now.
New dimensions, new portals to blow up. Shell we?
We are getting close. But the biggest boom is still waiting. Let's do it.
You will probably start here.
So you progressed and now you would like to learn more about the magic involved? Welcome.
Technology is the next magic. Let's end this show.
There are small mods present which are here just for your better fun. It is your job to explore them, but my job to tell you they are in.
